The article discusses the response of the United States to the coronavirus pandemic. President Trump has emphasized the country's strong healthcare system and the massive federal response being coordinated. The government has taken various public health actions and implemented economic measures to support American workers and small businesses. The CARES Act provides tax-free payments to qualifying families, along with additional funds for each child. The Paycheck Protection Program aims to keep Americans employed by offering forgivable loans for qualifying expenses. The article expresses gratitude towards healthcare workers and acknowledges the upcoming peak of the pandemic. Vice President Pence mentions the power of prayer and expresses optimism about the situation, attributing it to the efforts of the American people.